Mediator Design Pattern
foreign
is a part of a behavioral design pattern and as the name suggests it behaves as a mediator between the different kinds of
objects and different types of behaviors so that's the basic idea let's first understand what is mediator let's take
the real world example let's take the example of a ATC and the different planes revolving around and trying to
land okay so there are two to three planes which wants to land on an airport and what they do is they cannot talk
directly between them right because there might be chances of miscommunication as well and there might be other different challenges as well so
what they do is they talk to ADC okay ATC is a mediator and that ADC is
responsible to get the data from the different airplanes and to provide the data back to the different airplanes
based on the different status and notifications okay so that's the general idea so all the airplanes are connecting
to ADC and ADC is giving the information back to the pilots what should be done which plane should go first and all
those in information okay so that's the general idea and where ATC is the mediator so in our programming as well
this type of situation happens where multiple objects are graded and there are a lot of dependencies and everything
and because of that application gets tightly coupled and when the application gets tightly coupled the communication
between the different objects and how separately you can create those becomes very tedious right so at that time what
we do is we try to have a mediator and that mediator is responsible to have the
communication around the different objects okay so that's the same idea that we are going to use in the media
reticent Button as well okay so when you have different objects and you have very huge amount of dependencies and to
